channels.description:
The event known as the "Safar e Karbala" refers to the journey of the grandson of the Prophet Muhammad, Imam Hussain ibn Ali, and his family from Mecca to Karbala, where they were ultimately killed in a battle against the Umayyad caliph Yazid I in 680 CE. This event is considered one of the most significant events in Islamic history and is observed by Shia Muslims around the world as a day of mourning and remembrance.

The journey of Imam Hussain and his family from Mecca to Karbala is remembered for its tragic and poignant events, including the deprivation of food, water, and shelter that they faced along the way. The journey is also remembered for the bravery and sacrifice of Imam Hussain and his followers, who refused to submit to the unjust rule of Yazid I and fought for the principles of justice and righteousness.

The Safar e Karbala is observed annually by Shia Muslims through various rituals and traditions, including processions, mourning ceremonies, and recitations of poetry and other religious texts. It is a time for reflection and contemplation on the importance of standing up for one's beliefs and the value of sacrifice and selflessness.

karbala waqiya jo ke Islam ki tareekh ka aik ahem hadsa hai, 10 October 680 AD (Muharram 10, 61 AH) ko Karbala, Iraq mein hua tha. Is jang ka muqabla Imam Husayn ibn Ali ke chand sipahiyo aur unke ghar walon ke sath, aur Umayyad khalifa Yazid I ki taqatwar lashkar ke darmiyan tha.
channels.name: Safar e Karbala

channels.description: Bilal, a New Breed of Hero is a film made on the life of Hazrat Bilal ibn Rabah (R. A). Remember After Muhammad (P.B.U.H) died in 632 CE. Bilal was one of the people who did not give bay'ah (the oath of allegiance) to Abu Bakr. Umar ibn al-Khattab took Bilal by his clothes and said, "This is the reward of Abu Bakr. He has given you freedom, and now you do not want to follow him." Bilal said, "If Abu Bakr had emancipated me for the pleasure of Allah, then let him leave me alone for Allah but if he had given me freedom for his pleasure, then I am ready to render him the services required." But I am not going to pay allegiance to a person whom the Messenger of God had not appointed as his caliph, however it is not shown in this film.
channels.name: Bilal - A New Breed of Hero
channels.chapter_title: Bilal - A New Breed of Hero

channels.description: Al-Nebras (The Lantern) is a greatly anticipated motion picture film masterfully depicting various events and occurrences in the remarkable life of Imam Ali (as). The film brilliantly illuminates the significant role that Imam Ali played alongside the Holy Prophet (saw), emphasizing his crucial and essential position in relation to the Islamic Message. The film artistically depicts significant battles from the early days of Islam to the plains of Ghadeer, where Imam Ali (a.s.) was chosen as the successor to the Holy Prophet (saw). Al-Nebras covers some of the innumerable qualities found in the personality of Imam Ali (a.s.) and comprehensively underlines his central position in the Islamic Message.
channels.name: Al Nebras

channels.description: An eight-year-old Kashmiri girl 'Nooreh' lives in a small village on the India-Pakistan border. She believes that she has discovered a solution to end the cross-fire. Set in Kashmir, the film introduces us to young Nooreh whose life in a small village on the Indian-Pakistani border is disrupted by daily crossfire. One night, Nooreh discovers that she can control the gun battle by keeping her eyes open and vows to constantly stay awake. Restrained and well observed, the film offers an intimate look at daily life in a place where children play by counting bullet holes in the school building. With a sensitive lens and a rich soundscape, writer/director Ashish Pandey weaves together themes of violence and fantasy, giving us a rare insight into a child's mind and the subliminal effects of political conflict on its psyche.The film won the Sonje Award for Best Short at the Busan International Film Festival.
channels.name: Nooreh
